text.tspan: Dilemma is… fascinating, to say the very least. It
materialized one day inside the mansion and has never
left. When I first met it, I asked what its name was. It
stopped moving for about three whole minutes –
completely froze, not so much as a single muscle
twitched – and then said that it wanted to be named
Dilemma. I don’t think it even knows what that word
means. It has a strange obsession with two-
dimensional shapes, for whatever reason. It likes to
spend time with Stuart and Abby, who have welcomed
it into their friend group without a second thought.
